<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Sixth session 
Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>PROMOTION AND PROTECTION OF ALL HUMAN RIGHTS, 
CIVIL, POLITICAL, ECONOMIC, SOCIAL AND CULTURAL 
    RIGHTS, INCLUDING THE RIGHT TO DEVELOPMENT 
</b></p>
<p><b>Pakistan (on behalf of the Organization of the Islamic Conference): 
amendments to draft resolution L.15/Rev.1  
</b></p>
<p><b>Elimination of all forms of intolerance and of discrimination 
based on religion or belief 
</b></p>
<p>1. <b>Page 3 
</b></p>
<p> After the seventh preambular paragraph <i>insert 
</i></p>
<p><i>  Alarmed</i> at the recent instances of deliberate stereotyping of religions, their adherents 
and prophets in the media and by political parties and groups in some societies, 
</p>
<p>2. <b>Paragraph 8 
</b></p>
<p> The paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p> 8. <i>Emphasizes</i> that respect for and protection of all religions and beliefs, 
consistent with international law and national legislation, is a substantial element that is 
conducive to the exercise of the full enjoyment by all of the right to freedom of thought, 
conscience and religion; </p>

 <p> 
</p>
<p>3. <b>Paragraph 9 (a) 
</b></p>
<p><b>  </b><i>For</i> or the right to practise freely one&#8217;s religion, including the right to change one&#8217;s 
religion or belief <i>read</i> or the right to practise freely one&#8217;s religion 
</p>
<p>4. <b>Paragraph 16</b> 
</p>
<p> For the existing text <i>substitute</i> 
</p>
<p> 16. <i>Takes note</i> of the work of the Special Rapporteur on freedom of religion or 
belief; 
</p>
<p>5. <b>Paragraph 20</b> 
</p>
<p>  <i>For</i> to respond favourably <i>read</i> to consider responding favourably 
</p>
